ESP32-S3 is a low-power MCU-based system-on-chip (SoC) that supports 2.4 GHz Wi-Fi and Bluetooth® Low Energy (Bluetooth LE). It consists of high-performance dual-core microprocessor (Xtensa® 32-bit LX7), a low power coprocessor, a Wi-Fi baseband, a Bluetooth LE baseband, RF module, and peripherals.
Four pin crystal, GND on pins 2 and 4
CAN Bus Transceivers, 3.3V, 1Mbps, Low-Power capabilities, SOIC-8
TVS Diode Array, 5.5V Standoff, 3 Channels, SOT-143 package
coaxial connector (BNC, SMA, SMB, SMC, Cinch/RCA, LEMO, ...)
